<TITLE> Another BDR man dies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 17 (bdnews24.com) - A border guard from BDR's Pilkhana headquarters was reported dead Tuesday. "Monir Hossain, a member of Rifles Security Unit, was admitted to the BDR Hospital after falling ill," sub-inspector of Lalbagh Police Station, Delwar Hossain, told bdnews24.com, quoting a senior official. "He was transferred to Dhaka Medical College Hospital at around 3.30pm today, where doctors declared him dead at around 4:25pm," said the police officer. He said the autopsy would be carried out after he made a surathal (on the spot/appearance on death) examination in presence of a magistrate. A BDR soldier was reported to have committed suicide by hanging at the Joypurhat-based Battalion-3 on Monday and another to have hung himself within the Pilkhana headquarters on Mar 9. bdne
